text: a = [1,2,6,3,1,4]  b= [] length = len(a) count1 = 0 count = 0 for i in range(0,length):     count = 0     for j in range(i):         if a[i]<a[j]:             count = count + 1     if count > 0:            b.append(a[i])         count1 = count1 + 1            print('Input List  ', a) print('List with Sorted Element  ', b) print('Total count of unsorted Element =',count1)    Output: Input Line   [1, 2, 6, 3, 1, 4] List with Unsorted Element   [3, 1, 4] Total count of unsorted Element = 3

author: @pream90
text: ## Bubble sort compare the adjacent element and push highest number to extreme position  ## Time complexity o(n2) best case o(n)(when array is already sorted) c=[1,2,3,4,5,7,2,8] n=len(c) k=0  for i in range(0,n-1):     m=0         for j in range(0, n-i-1):                  if(c[j]>c[j+1]):             c[j],c[j+1]=c[j+1],c[j]             k=k+1             print(" array is not sorted already")             m=1     if(m==0):         break     else:         continue print("number of unsorted numbers are",k) print("Sorted array is",c)

text: Hi Krish ,  Here is my solution ,  ## Bubble sort c=[1,2,7,14,3,2,8] n=len(c) k=0 for i in range(0,n-1):     for j in range(0, n-i-1):         if(c[j]>c[j+1]):             c[j],c[j+1]=c[j+1],c[j]             k=k+1 print("number of unsorted numbers are",k) print("Sorted array is",c)
